<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880627-0151 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor: Are Tobacco Firms Buying Respectability? </HL><SO> </SO><IN> TOB </IN><TEXT>   Your article &quot;Blowing Smoke: Tobacco Firms, Pariahs to Many People, Still Are Angels to the Arts&quot; (page one, June 8) presents a tantalizing view of the campaign by Philip Morris to buy respectability by making substantial donations to the art community. The fact remains that cigarette smoking is responsible for infinitely greater health-care costs to the body politic as well as untold pain and suffering to millions of its victims.    Richard Sinsheimer   Beverly Hills, Calif.   ---   A partial solution to this problem is simple: Have our elected representatives stop all subsidies to tobacco growers and allocate those funds to the arts.    Emil J. Klingenfus   Augusta, Ga.</TEXT></DOC>